{
  "texts": [
    "The architecture of the DETR model consists of two parts, the backbone part (e.g., ResNet50, a convolutional neural network) extracting features and the transformer part (as object detection head) predicting bounding boxes and classes from the features extracted by the backbone.",
    "In our experiment, we replace the static ResNet50 backbone part of the DETR model with the dynamic OFA-ResNet50 (once-for-all architecture) (Cai et al. 2020), which allows us to switch between different sub-networks of the OFA-ResNet50 dynamically on-the-fly.",
    "Similar to Sect. 7, we consider 16 DNN variants or sub-networks in OFA-ResNet50, supporting 16 different input (data) sizes (in both spatial dimensions) from 128 to 608 with a step size of 32.",
    "We then add one transformer block as an object detection head to all 16 OFA-ResNet50 sub-networks (backbones), generating 16 OFA-ResNet50-DETR variants.",
    "The latency and throughput profiles of every OFA-ResNet50-DETR variant are similar to the profiles of YOLOv4 DNNs (see Sect. 7.1)."
  ]
}